Core.CruiseName: Tokt Test - Akvaplan-NIVA AS & University of Bergen
Core.Abstract: <p data-start="254" data-end="397">The primary objective of this cruise is to conduct&nbsp;<strong data-start="305" data-end="343">long-term environmental monitoring</strong>&nbsp;in the Northeast Atlantic. Activities will include:</p><ul data-start="399" data-end="835"><li data-start="399" data-end="516"><p data-start="401" data-end="516"><strong data-start="401" data-end="426">Water Column Sampling</strong>&nbsp;using CTD rosettes to collect physical and chemical parameters for baseline monitoring.</p></li><li data-start="517" data-end="604"><p data-start="519" data-end="604"><strong data-start="519" data-end="542">Biological Sampling</strong>&nbsp;with plankton collections to assess ecosystem productivity.</p></li><li data-start="605" data-end="714"><p data-start="607" data-end="714"><strong data-start="607" data-end="627">Seafloor Surveys</strong>&nbsp;using demersal and pelagic trawls to evaluate benthic habitats and fish populations.</p></li><li data-start="715" data-end="835"><p data-start="717" data-end="835"><strong data-start="717" data-end="739">Technology Testing</strong>&nbsp;of the Toktlogger/Cruiseline system for improved cruise data logging and project integration.</p></li></ul><p data-start="837" data-end="1036">The cruise will also provide data for ongoing&nbsp;<strong data-start="883" data-end="904">monitoring series</strong>, contribute to national marine research priorities, and support international collaboration through standardized data collection.</p>
